                    "kind": "text",
                    "data": "Now I have a thorough understanding of the codebase. Let me summarize what I see and ask clarifying questions.\n\n---\n\nHere's my understanding: You want to implement a **full-page overlay/workspace** that opens when clicking an existing appointment card on the dashboard. The design feedback from `image_6c9d39.png` suggests this should be a dedicated clinical workspace — not just a detail drawer — that gives the practitioner room for tooth charts, notes, and treatment history. You want this built in both the **design system prototype** (`ui_kits/website/dashboard.html`) and the **production React app** (`frontend/src/`).\n\nBefore I plan this out, I have a few questions:\n\n**[1]**: Which interaction pattern do you want for clicking an appointment card?\n- a. **Full-page overlay** — Clicking the card immediately opens a full-page clinical workspace (tooth chart, notes, treatment history, status actions). A \"Back to Dashboard\" button returns.\n- b. **Hybrid (inline expand → full-page)** — Clicking the card first expands it inline to show quick actions (Check-in, Open Chart, Reschedule). Clicking \"Open Chart\" then triggers the full-page workspace.\n- c. **Other** — Describe your preferred flow.\n\n**[2]**: Where should this be built?\n- a. **Design system prototype only** (`dashboard.html`) — A static/interactive HTML mock of the full-page workspace.\n- b. **Production React app only** (`frontend/src/`) — Wire the appointment card click in the Dashboard to navigate to the existing `Patient360` page (or a new appointment workspace route).\n- c. **Both** — Design system prototype first, then production React implementation.\n\n**[3]**: What clinical data should the full-page workspace show? The existing `Patient360` already has tabs for Overview, Appointments, Documents, Insurance, Treatment Plans, Lab Cases, Communications, and Notes. Should the appointment workspace:\n- a. **Reuse Patient360** — Navigate to `/patients/:id` with the appointment context pre-loaded (e.g., auto-open the relevant tab).\n- b. **New appointment-focused workspace** — A dedicated layout with the appointment at the center: patient header, tooth chart, SOAP notes editor, status actions, and treatment plan — all visible without tabs.\n- c. **Other** — Describe what you envision."
