                    "data": "Good. Now I have a complete picture. Let me ask the remaining clarifying questions based on your answers:\n\nYou said:\n1. **c (Other)** for the interaction pattern — can you describe what you want? Just clicking the appointment card opens a full-page overlay focused on that specific appointment?\n2. **a** — Design system prototype only (`dashboard.html`)\n3. **c (Other)** — Focus on the selected appointment\n\nLet me ask follow-up questions to nail down the full-page workspace content:\n\n**[1]**: For the full-page appointment workspace, what sections should be visible when you click an appointment card (e.g., \"Alice Stevens · 08:30 · Recall · 6mo\")?\n- a. **Compact clinical view** — Appointment header (patient avatar + name + time + procedure + status), tooth chart, and status action buttons (Confirm, Check-in, Start, Complete, No-show, Cancel, Reschedule). Focused on the single appointment.\n- b. **Rich clinical view** — Everything in (a) plus a SOAP notes area and treatment history/plan section for that visit.\n- c. **Other** — Describe what you want on the page.\n\n**[2]**: For the transition animation when clicking an appointment card, what do you prefer?\n- a. **Fade + slide up** — The dashboard fades out and the workspace slides up (400ms ease-out per the design system motion tokens).\n- b. **Shared element transition** — The clicked appointment card animates/expands to become the workspace header (the \"visual tether\" mentioned in the feedback).\n- c. **Simple crossfade** — Dashboard fades out, workspace fades in.\n\n**[3]**: Should the \"Back to Dashboard\" button be:\n- a. **Top-left arrow + text** — A back arrow with \"Back to Dashboard\" label in the workspace header.\n- b. **X close button** — Same pattern as the drawer close button, top-right.\n- c. **Both** — Back arrow top-left AND X button top-right."
