                        "plan": "\n**Implementation Plan — Full-Page Appointment Workspace (Design System Prototype)**\n\n**Problem Statement:**\nWhen clicking an existing appointment card on the dashboard, the current behavior opens a simple `DetailDrawer` (right-side panel with key-value rows). The goal is to replace this with a full-page overlay workspace focused on the selected appointment, providing a compact clinical view with appointment header, tooth chart, and status action buttons. This is design system prototype work only (`dashboard.html`).\n\n**Requirements:**\n- Clicking an appointment card opens a full-page overlay (not a drawer) focused on that appointment\n- The workspace shows: appointment header (patient avatar + name + time + procedure + status), tooth chart, and status action buttons (Confirm, Check-in, Start, Complete, No-show, Cancel, Reschedule)\n- Transition: fade + slide up (400ms ease-out per design system motion tokens)\n- \"Back to Dashboard\" button: top-left arrow + text label\n- Design system prototype only — `dashboard.html` in `ui_kits/website/`\n- Follow all design system tokens from `colors_and_type.css` — no raw hex outside existing token values\n- Brand voice: authoritative, clinical, calm. No emoji.\n\n**Background:**\n- The file is at: frontend/design_system/rockyridgeai-dental.com/ui_kits/website/dashboard.html\n- The dashboard currently uses `setDetail(...)` → `DetailDrawer` for appointment card clicks\n- The `DetailDrawer` is a generic right-side drawer with key-value rows — also used for patients, invoices, and lab cases\n- The `ToothChartTile` component already exists in the design system with FDI numbering and status fills\n- The `AppointmentCard` component provides the appointment data shape: `{ id, time, duration, patient_id, patient, provider, chair, kind, status }`\n- Status tones are already defined in `AppointmentCard.jsx`: confirmed (green), pending (amber), no_show (red), completed (grey)\n- Design system motion: `--duration-slow: 400ms`, `--ease-out: cubic-bezier(0.16, 1, 0.3, 1)`\n- The `drawer-back` CSS class was already added in the previous change set\n- CLAUDE.md rules: Use design system tokens from colors_and_type.css, never raw hex in components. Light theme for clinical surfaces. No emoji, no filled icons, no playful easing. Brand voice: authoritative, clinical, calm.\n\n**Proposed Solution:**\n1. Add CSS for the full-page workspace overlay (`.appt-workspace`, animation keyframes)\n2. Create an `AppointmentWorkspace` component that renders the full-page view for a selected appointment\n3. Change the `Dashboard` component to use `setActiveAppt(appointment)` instead of `setDetail(...)` for appointment card clicks, rendering `AppointmentWorkspace` when an appointment is selected\n4. Keep `DetailDrawer` intact for patients, invoices, and lab cases — only appointment cards change behavior\n\n**Task Breakdown:**\n\nTask 1: Add CSS for the full-page appointment workspace\n- Clear objective: Add CSS rules for `.appt-workspace` (full-page overlay), `.appt-ws-header`, `.appt-ws-body`, `.appt-ws-actions`, and a `@keyframes wsEnter` animation (fade + slide up, 400ms)\n- Implementation: Insert after the existing `.drawer-back:hover` rule block, before `/* Toast */`. Use design system tokens (`--ease-out`, `--duration-slow`, `--rr-warm-white`, `--rr-parchment`, etc.). The workspace is `position: fixed; inset: 0; z-index: 40; background: var(--rr-warm-white)` with the slide-up animation.\n- The CSS to insert after `.drawer-back:hover { background: var(--rr-off-white); color: var(--rr-ink); }` and before `/* Toast */`:\n\n```css\n  /* Appointment workspace (full-page overlay) */\n  @keyframes wsEnter { from { opacity: 0; transform: translateY(16px); } to { opacity: 1; transform: translateY(0); } }\n  .appt-workspace { position: fixed; inset: 0; z-index: 40; background: var(--rr-warm-white); display: flex; flex-direction: column; animation: wsEnter 400ms cubic-bezier(0.16, 1, 0.3, 1); }\n  .appt-ws-topbar { padding: 14px 28px; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--rr-parchment); display: flex; align-items: center; background: #fff; }\n  .appt-ws-topbar .back-label { font-family: var(--font-ui); font-size: .85rem; color: var(--rr-slate-dark); }\n  .appt-ws-topbar .drawer-back:hover ~ .back-label, .appt-ws-topbar:hover .back-label { color: var(--rr-ink); }\n  .appt-ws-body { flex: 1; overflow-y: auto; padding: 28px 32px; display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 24px; max-width: 1200px; margin: 0 auto; width: 100%; box-sizing: border-box; }\n  .appt-ws-hero { background: #fff; border: 1px solid var(--rr-parchment); border-radius: 6px; padding: 22px 24px; display: grid; grid-template-columns: 48px 1fr auto; gap: 18px; align-items: center; box-shadow: var(--shadow-xs); }\n  .appt-ws-ava { width: 48px; height: 48px; border-radius: 999px; background: hsl(var(--primary)); color: #fff; display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center; font-weight: 700; font-size: 1rem; flex-shrink: 0; }\n  .appt-ws-info { display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 3px; }\n  .appt-ws-name { font-family: var(--font-display); font-weight: 700; font-size: 1.2rem; color: var(--rr-navy-800); }\n  .appt-ws-detail { font-family: var(--font-ui); font-size: .82rem; color: var(--rr-slate-dark); }\n  .appt-ws-id { font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: .72rem; color: var(--rr-slate-dark); }\n  .appt-ws-actions { display: flex; flex-wrap: wrap; gap: 8px; }\n```\n\n- Test: Visual — open dashboard.html, confirm no CSS errors.\n- Demo: CSS loads without errors; no visual change yet since no component uses the classes.\n\nTask 2: Create the `AppointmentWorkspace` component\n- Clear objective: Build a React component that receives an appointment object and `onClose` callback, rendering a full-page overlay with: (1) a top bar with back-arrow + \"Back to Dashboard\" label, (2) an appointment header showing patient avatar/initials, patient name, appointment ID, time, duration, procedure, provider, operatory, and status badge, (3) the `ToothChartTile` component, and (4) a row of status action buttons (Confirm, Check-in, Start, Complete, No-show, Cancel, Reschedule).\n- Implementation: Insert the component definition BEFORE the `Dashboard` component (i.e., before `const Dashboard = () => {`). Use the existing `drawer-back` class for the back button. Reuse the status tone map inline (same values as AppointmentCard.jsx: confirmed green, pending amber, no_show red, completed grey). The tooth chart is the existing `<ToothChartTile />`. Action buttons use `btn btn-ghost btn-md` and `btn btn-primary btn-md` classes. ESC key closes the workspace.\n\nThe component code to insert before `const Dashboard = () => {`:\n\n```jsx\nconst WS_STATUS = {\n  confirmed: { bg: '#E8F5EE', fg: '#2A7D4F', label: 'Confirmed' },\n  pending:   { bg: '#FDF3E5', fg: '#B45309', label: 'Pending'   },\n  no_show:   { bg: '#F8E5E8', fg: '#9B2335', label: 'No-show'   },\n  completed: { bg: '#F5F2EC', fg: '#4A5568', label: 'Completed' },\n};\n\nconst AppointmentWorkspace = ({ appointment, onClose }) => {\n  const a = appointment;\n  const tone = WS_STATUS[a.status] || WS_STATUS.confirmed;\n  const initials = a.patient.split(' ').map(s => s[0]).slice(0, 2).join('').toUpperCase();\n\n  React.useEffect(() => {\n    const h = e => e.key === 'Escape' && onClose();\n    document.addEventListener('keydown', h);\n    return () => document.removeEventListener('keydown', h);\n  }, [onClose]);\n\n  return (\n    <div className=\"appt-workspace\">\n      <div className=\"appt-ws-topbar\">\n        <button className=\"drawer-back\" onClick={onClose}>\n          <svg width=\"18\" height=\"18\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"currentColor\" strokeWidth=\"1.5\"><path d=\"M19 12H5\"/><path d=\"M12 19l-7-7 7-7\"/></svg>\n        </button>\n        <span className=\"back-label\">Back to Dashboard</span>\n      </div>\n      <div className=\"appt-ws-body\">\n        <div className=\"appt-ws-hero\">\n          <div className=\"appt-ws-ava\">{initials}</div>\n          <div className=\"appt-ws-info\">\n            <div className=\"appt-ws-name\">{a.patient}</div>\n            <div className=\"appt-ws-detail\">{a.kind} · {a.provider} · Op {a.chair} · {a.time} — {a.duration} min</div>\n            <div className=\"appt-ws-id\">{a.id} · {a.patient_id}</div>\n          </div>\n          <span style={{ fontSize: '.68rem', fontWeight: 600, padding: '4px 12px', borderRadius: 4, letterSpacing: '.06em', textTransform: 'uppercase', background: tone.bg, color: tone.fg, alignSelf: 'flex-start' }}>{tone.label}</span>\n        </div>\n        <div className=\"appt-ws-actions\">\n          <button className=\"btn btn-primary btn-md\">Confirm</button>\n          <button className=\"btn btn-ghost btn-md\">Check in</button>\n          <button className=\"btn btn-ghost btn-md\">Start</button>\n          <button className=\"btn btn-ghost btn-md\">Complete</button>\n          <button className=\"btn btn-ghost btn-md\">No show</button>\n          <button className=\"btn btn-ghost btn-md\">Reschedule</button>\n          <button className=\"btn btn-ghost btn-md\" style={{ color: 'var(--rr-error)' }}>Cancel</button>\n        </div>\n        <ToothChartTile />\n      </div>\n    </div>\n  );\n};\n```\n\n- Test: Visual — component renders correctly when called with a sample appointment.\n- Demo: The `AppointmentWorkspace` component exists and can be rendered.\n\nTask 3: Wire appointment card clicks to the workspace and keep DetailDrawer for other entities\n- Clear objective: In the `Dashboard` component, add `activeAppt` state. Change the `AppointmentCard` `onClick` to `setActiveAppt(a)` instead of `setDetail(...)`. Render `{activeAppt && <AppointmentWorkspace appointment={activeAppt} onClose={() => setActiveAppt(null)} />}` alongside the existing `detail && <DetailDrawer ...>` (which still handles patients, invoices, lab cases).\n- Implementation changes in Dashboard:\n