-ease-out: cubic-bezier(0.16, 1, 0.3, 1)`\n- The `drawer-back` CSS class was already added in the previous change set\n\n**Proposed Solution:**\n1. Add CSS for the full-page workspace overlay (`.appt-workspace`, animation keyframes)\n2. Create an `AppointmentWorkspace` component that renders the full-page view for a selected appointment\n3. Change the `Dashboard` component to use `setActiveAppt(appointment)` instead of `setDetail(...)` for appointment card clicks, rendering `AppointmentWorkspace` when an appointment is selected\n4. Keep `DetailDrawer` intact for patients, invoices, and lab cases — only appointment cards change behavior\n\n**Task Breakdown:**\n\nTask 1: Add CSS for the full-page appointment workspace\n- Clear objective: Add CSS rules for `.appt-workspace` (full-page overlay), `.appt-ws-header`, `.appt-ws-body`, `.appt-ws-actions`, and a `@keyframes wsEnter` animation (fade + slide up, 400ms)\n- Implementation: Insert after the existing `.drawer-back:hover` rule block, before `/* Toast */`. Use design system tokens (`--ease-out`, `--duration-slow`, `--rr-warm-white`, `--rr-parchment`, etc.). The workspace is `position: fixed; inset: 0; z-index: 40; background: var(--rr-warm-white)` with the slide-up animation.\n- Test: Visual — open dashboard.html, confirm no CSS errors, workspace styles are defined.\n- Demo: CSS loads without errors; no visual change yet since no component uses the classes.\n\nTask 2: Create the `AppointmentWorkspace` component\n- Clear objective: Build a React component that receives an appointment object and `onClose` callback, rendering a full-page overlay with: (1) a top bar with back-arrow + \"Back to Dashboard\" label, (2) an appointment header showing patient avatar/initials, patient name, appointment ID, time, duration, procedure, provider, operatory, and status badge, (3) the `ToothChartTile` component, and (4) a row of status action buttons (Confirm, Check-in, Start, Complete, No-show, Cancel, Reschedule).\n- Implementation